<div id="review_2847689900" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2847689900" />
    <a title="Cliff Moyce" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30565584-cliff-moyce"><img alt="Cliff Moyce" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1583920534p2/30565584.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2847689900?book_show_action=true">Jun 26, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cliff Moyce" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cliff Moyce" href="/user/show/30565584-cliff-moyce">Cliff Moyce</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2847689900" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8690442936095444089">I have been practising ‘western’ mindfulness meditation (using the popular apps) for the three years that I have been suffering from acute chronic pain (following disastrous spinal surgery). It made no difference to my pain, and I was starting to wish et why I was doing it. This book places mindfulness and other techniques / approaches in the context of the teachings of the Buddha, and in doing so it all started to make sense to me. It added to my repertoire of tips, tricks and techniques for le</span>
  <span id="freeText8690442936095444089" style="display:none">I have been practising ‘western’ mindfulness meditation (using the popular apps) for the three years that I have been suffering from acute chronic pain (following disastrous spinal surgery). It made no difference to my pain, and I was starting to wish et why I was doing it. This book places mindfulness and other techniques / approaches in the context of the teachings of the Buddha, and in doing so it all started to make sense to me. It added to my repertoire of tips, tricks and techniques for leading a better life while in pain, as well as introducing me to other writers and teachers on the subject. Part of this involves getting rid of unhelpful habits, including stopping ‘boom and bust’ behaviours.<br />It is a shame that Toni became chronically ill, but in doing so she has given back to the world even more than she was doing already as a professor of law. Her bad luck became our good luck.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8690442936095444089" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


